Package InfrastructureManager.Modules.AdvantEDGE.Output.NetworkCharacteristic

Class NetworkEvent

java.lang.Object
InfrastructureManager.Modules.AdvantEDGE.Output.NetworkCharacteristic.NetworkEvent
public class NetworkEvent
extends java.lang.Object
Class that represents a network event to an element in an AdvantEdge deployment.

A network event consists of two parts: - The element affected - The NetworkParameters that will determine the event

    • NetworkEvent

      public NetworkEvent​(java.lang.String elementName, java.lang.String elementType, NetworkParameters netChar)
      Creates a new NetworkEvent object based on the affected element and the network characteristics to update
      Parameters:
      elementName - Name of the affected element
      elementType - Type of the element to apply the new NW characteristics. It can be any valid element in an AdvantEdge deployment (e.g FOG,UE, etc.)
      netChar - Network characteristics that will be updated
